5. 'tiridates became king of Parthia for a short time in succession to Phraates or Prahates IV., who was expelled. It seems that Tiridates raised a rebellion against Phraates about B.c. 33, and after some unsuc- cessful campaigns fled (B.c. 30) to Octavianus (then passing through Syria after the battle of Actium). From Syria he afterwards made

another attempt and managed to expel Phraates in Rc. 27. Phraates, however, recovered the throne early in B.c. 26. There are allusions to the same events in 11. 2. 17 and 111. 8. 19.
